<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The struct member pos->header is declared as 'char *header' but in this fragment it is only used for read-only comparison (MHD_str_equal_caseless_bin_n_(pos->header, key, ...)). Under MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13 the pointer should be const-qualified when possible (e.g. 'const char *header'), so having it as 'char *' when it is only read constitutes a violation. (Note: if the header buffer is actually modified elsewhere, making it const may be infeasible; the violation applies when the object is effectively immutable and should be declared const.)
</scenario>
